<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px"><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center"><tr><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" ><a name="post8398"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/tdg/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a> 06-12-2003, 04:49 PM</td><td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">&nbsp;#<a href="showpost.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;p=8398&amp;postcount=13" target="new"><strong>13</strong></a></td></tr><tr valign="top"><td class="alt2" width="175"><div id="postmenu_8398">Demasia</div><div class="smallfont">Guest</div><div class="smallfont">&nbsp;<br /><div>Posts: n/a</div><div>   </div></div></td><td class="alt1"><div class="smallfont"> 	<strong>Re: The Rez Issue: Brainstorming</strong></div><hr size="1" style="color:" /><div><br /> <strong>GY and Zoneline Rez?</strong><br />
<br />
Clerics do not have a monopoly on healing. Healing is tied with damage, in the number of classes that can do it. If it is done through spells, skills, or even bandages.<br />
<br />
Clerics just happen to be the best at healing.<br />
<br />
The next thing you could say clerics have a monopoly is rezes. But that makes as much sense as saying wizards have the monopoly on tps. It just doesn't make sense.<br />
<br />
You have druids purposing having a rez NPC at the GYs of PoP. You have clerics agreeing with the idea. Whats wrong with that? <br />
<br />
A soulbinder has been set up to alleviate the hassle of melees looking for a bind. Its not as good as bind but it does real nice as a replacement.<br />
<br />
A modified tp system has set up via PoK books to alleviate some of the hassle of travel? Its not as good as teleport but it does real nice as a replacement.<br />
<br />
Why not set up a modified rez system? Something not as good as the original, but it does alleviate the NEED for a cleric.<br />
<br />
Divina <br /></div></td></tr><tr><td class="alt2"> 	 &nbsp;</td><td class="alt1" align="right"><a href="newreply.php?s=0ae560748df707a3dc376beb25709ebc&amp;do=newreply&amp;p=8398"><img src="images/tdg/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" /></a> 	</td></tr></table><div class="vbmenu_popup" id="postmenu_8398_menu" style="display:none"><table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"><tr><td class="thead">Demasia</td></tr></table></div></div>
